# Material UI Best Practices

## Imports

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - Direct named imports from @mui/material
import Card from '@mui/material/Card';
import Table from '@mui/material/Table';
import TableBody from '@mui/material/TableBody';
import Icon from '@mui/material/Icon';

// ✅ GOOD - Icons from @mui/icons-material when using specific icons
import EditIcon from '@mui/icons-material/Edit';
import DeleteIcon from '@mui/icons-material/Delete';

// ❌ BAD - Barrel imports (hurts tree-shaking)
import { Card, Table } from '@mui/material';
```

## Styling

- Prefer `sx` prop for one-off styles; use `styled()` for reusable styled components
- Use theme values via `sx`: `sx={{ color: 'primary.main', typography: 'body1' }}`
- For custom theme tokens, reference `theme.palette`, `theme.typography`, `theme.spacing`

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - sx for inline styles
<Card sx={{ p: 2, borderRadius: 2 }}>
  <Typography variant="body1" color="text.secondary">
    Content
  </Typography>
</Card>

// ✅ GOOD - styled() for reusable components
import { styled } from '@mui/material/styles';
const StyledCard = styled(Card)(({ theme }) => ({
  borderRadius: theme.shape.borderRadius * 2,
}));
```

## Project Conventions

- Use **Soft UI** components when available: `SoftBox`, `SoftTypography`, `SoftButton`, `SoftInput`, etc.
- Use `Icon` from `@mui/material/Icon` with `children` for icon names (e.g. `"edit"`, `"delete"`) when using Material Icons font
- Use `@mui/icons-material` for SVG icons when you need a specific icon component

## Layout & Spacing

- Use `Box` for layout; prefer `sx` over `style` for consistency with theme
- Use `theme.spacing()` or numeric shorthand: `sx={{ p: 2, mt: 1 }}` (1 = 8px by default)

## Tables

- Use `TableContainer` > `Table` > `TableHead`/`TableBody` > `TableRow` > `TableCell`
- Use `Collapse` for expandable rows

## Dialogs

- Use `Dialog`, `DialogTitle`, `DialogContent`, `DialogActions` for modals
- Provide `aria-labelledby` and `aria-describedby` for accessibility when needed
